I started doing "desk" research on the idea i.e. to check that there was actually a market and demand for the product ... so i was looking at existing reports that are out there and what the government thinks about careers services in schools etc

then i started networking my heart out! Messaging people that were quite senior in the industry and seeing who would respond (and refining my message as i got to understand what people responded to the most)

and asked them for a quick coffee for feedback on my idea. As you can imagine A LOT of people ignore your messages, but 1 or 2 start replying and can then, once you've had coffee, they recommend you meet someone else they know, etc, etc. and it snowballs from there
so lots of research first

then its about speaking to CUSTOMERS ... so i started reaching out to schools and students and getting their feedback on little surveys etc which helped me make hypotheses about what people actually want out of e-mentors
